root: ^Uranus is the seventh planet from the Sun.
^It is named after Greek sky deity Uranus (Caelus), who in Greek mythology is the father of Cronus (Saturn),
^a grandfather of Zeus (Jupiter) and great-grandfather of Ares (Mars).
^Uranus has the third-largest planetary radius and fourth-largest planetary mass in the Solar System.
^The planet is similar in composition to Neptune, and both have bulk chemical compositions which differ from those of the other two giant planets,
^Jupiter and Saturn (the gas giants). For this reason, scientists often distinguish Uranus and Neptune as "ice giants".
